spans.text: While Spring eternal , on the lilied plain , Waves amber radiance through the fields of air
in your greenwood bowers they love to dwell
in your vales they swell the choral song
The guardian nymphs of green Parnassus
The guardian nymphs of green Parnassus
The murmuring wreaths of cool Cephisus
, a smiling band , Crowned with the fragrant wreaths of rosy flowers
The land where Heaven's own hallowed waters play , Where Friendship binds the generous and the good ,
what remorse thy maddening thoughts shall sting
Think what remorse thy maddening thoughts shall sting , When dying pangs their gentle bosoms tear
thy bosom melt to Pity's cry
In dust we kneel — by sacred Heaven
No ! let thy bosom melt to Pity's cry , — In dust we kneel — by sacred Heaven implore — OH ! stop thy lifted arm , ere yet they die , Nor dip thy horrid hands in infant gore !
glory ! — Rise , — forbid , — avert the blow ! — In these vales of placid gladness Let no rueful maniac range
